lly, if a class is already reachable, JaCoCo might filter it out during dynamic access reports, even if \\\"call site covered\\\" should catch any invocation. I'm curious to explore this further!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring Class.forName behavior**\\n\\nI’m considering why Class.forName might not be capturing coverage as expected. Could it be that native substitution is folding it into a constant? Maybe using class$ with a class name that isn’t reachable plays a role, but does it really need dynamic metadata?\\n\\nIf Class.forName is called on a test class, the dynamic access report is supposed to note that, but could the target be getting filtered out? I'm also thinking about using a library class that isn't statically referenced in tests, yet I’d still need an assertion. This is a bit puzzling!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting Jacoco coverage**\\n\\nI think the TCK report likely only measures call sites from the code that's being tested. There might be a line like `class$(CsrfTokenFinder.groovy)` in the code, but if it's called via Method.invoke, then Jacoco coverage shows that the class$ method is covered. I'll need to check the Jacoco effective XML to get a clearer picture of how coverage is represented. Getting this right is crucial, so I'll proceed carefully!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_qD6VleSEq3PG3MCFZEEwmoB1|fc_09e80d339dd84ba4016a28138f4238819388439b5754922255", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/build/reports/jacoco -type f | head -20 && grep -R \"findCsrfFormToken_closure2\" -n tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/build/reports/jacoco tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/build/jacoco 2>/dev/null | head -30", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 288, "output": 1654, "cacheRead": 47616, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 49558, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0,